This paper deals with machine learning applications in gait analysis, which involves processing and analyzing human movement data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of different data preprocessing methods on classification accuracy, which is relevant to the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The study also involves human subjects, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
